Column Comment.0: UNIQUE WELL IDENTIFIER: A unique name, code or number designated as theprimary key for this row.
Column Comment.1: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.2: PRESSURE OBSERVATION NUMBER: A sequence number uniquely identifying theproduction test being performed in the well.
Column Comment.3: ABSOLUTE OPEN FLOW OBSERVATION NUMBER: A number identifying theabsolute open flow (AOF) pressure observation.
Column Comment.4: POINT OBSERVATION NUMBER: Unique number identifying the four point testobservation. Each point corresponds to a change in the choke size.
Column Comment.5: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.6: BOTTOM HOLE FLOW PRESSURE: Flowing pressure at or near the bottom of thewell.
Column Comment.7: BOTTOM HOLE FLOW PRESSURE OUOM: Bottom hole flowing pressure originalunit of measure.
Column Comment.8: CHOKE SIZE DESCRIPTION: Description of the choke size (e.g., 9 5/8 in). A valveor an orifice used to restrict or control the rate of flow.
Column Comment.9: CONDENSATE FLOW RATE: The flowing condensate rate recorded during a fourpoint test. Supports four point test data in which condensate has been extracted atthe separator during the flow period.
Column Comment.10: CONDENSATE FLOW RATE ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE
Column Comment.11: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.12: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.13: FINAL SHUTIN PRESSURE: The final shutin pressure recorded for the specific pointof the four point pressure test.
Column Comment.14: FINAL SHUTIN PRESSURE ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASUREMENT
Column Comment.15: FLOW DURATION: The duration of flow during the four point pressure test.
Column Comment.16: FLOW DURATION ORIGINAL UNIT OF MEASUREMENT
Column Comment.17: FLOW PRESSURE: Flowing tubing pressure recorded in conjunction with the variouschanges in the choke size during a four point test.
Column Comment.18: FLOW PRESSURE OUOM: Flowing pressure original unit of measure.
Column Comment.19: FLOW RATE: Flowing gas rate recorded in conjunction with changes of choke sizeduring a four point test.
Column Comment.20: FLOW RATE OUOM: Flow rate original unit of measure.
Column Comment.21: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.22: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.23: WATER FLOW RATE: The flowing water rate recorded during a four point test.Supports four point test data in which water has been extracted at the separatorduring the flow period.
Column Comment.24: WATER FLOW RATE ORIGINAL UNITS OF MEASURE
Column Comment.25: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.26: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.27: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.28: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.29: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.30: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.31: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
